OL,6,FConnell lied to officers telling them
OL,7,Fthat the man he described as his "dear
OL,8,Ffriend" was in Scotland and had given
OL,9,Fpermission to break-in and take the
OL,10,Fdog for a walk.
OL,12,FThe killer later changed his story
OL,13,Fclaiming he was upstairs in the house,
OL,14,Fasleep after taking heroin and crack,
OL,15,Fwhile someone else strangled Mr
OL,16,FPatience downstairs.
OL,18,FMichael Hayton KC, prosecuting, said
OL,19,FConnell preyed upon the good nature of
OL,20,FMr Patience, who had access to cash
OL,21,Ffrom family property.
